	<!-- Section: Welcome -->
	<section id="intro">

		<h1>Introduction</h1>
		<hr>

		<h4>Sass globbing allows you to import many Sass or Scss files in a single import statement. Mixture has support out of the box, no setup required.</h4>

	</section>

	<section id="example1">

		<h1>Sass</h1>
		<hr>
		<p class="callout callout-info">We've updated how this works in the latest version of Mixture, you need to activate globbing in the Mixture settings as per the following example: </p><pre class="prettyprint linenums pad" data-initialized="true" data-gclp-id="0"><ol class="linenums"><li class="L0"><span class="str">"sass"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="pun">{</span></li><li class="L1"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"globbing"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">true</span></li><li class="L2"><span class="pun">}</span></li></ol></pre><p></p>
		<p class="callout callout-info">For a full list of the settings for Sass <a href="/preprocessors#sass">please see the preprocessor section</a>.</p>
		<p>Once activated you can start adding your import statements:</p>
		<p>Import a folder of files:</p>
		<p><code>@import "library/mixins/*";</code></p>
		<p>If you have issues you can also try...</p>
		<p><code>@import "library/mixins/**";</code></p>
		<p>Import a tree of files:</p>
		<p><code>@import "library/mixins/**/*";</code></p>
		<p class="callout callout-info">Globbed files are sorted alphabetically before importing them and globs are always relative to the current file.</p>

	</section>

	<section id="example2" style="min-height: 147px;">

		<h1>Compass</h1>
		<hr>
		<p>To use Globbing in Mixture with compass you just need to adjust the <code>compass/config.rb</code> in the root of your project and add the following line at the top of the file <code>require 'sass-globbing'</code></p>
		<p>Once thats done the same logic applies as detailed above in Sass.</p>

	</section>

